				THE GOOD
			</h3>
			<p class="hidden"> 
				Music education sells itself. Study upon study illustrates the benefits of music instruction to child development. Children who receive musical instruction score higher on spatial-temporal tests than those in a control group. Reading ability and verbal memory has been shown to improve with a long enough exposure to music. In other words, the benefits reach far beyond the band room.
			</p>
