			<h3>
				THE NOT SO GOOD
			</h3>
			<p class="hidden">
				Music programs throughout the nation are in danger of being cut and many have already. Financially constrained districts must choose between a myriad of school programs as their budgets are diminishing. Music programs are seen as expensive to administer due to personnel and equipment costs. The value of musical programs is not seen unless communities rally and fight to keep them alive.
			</p>
